The `evaluationInfo` object in the Segmentation API controls which evaluation mode(s) are enabled for a segment definition. Setting `evaluationInfo.continuous.enabled: true` creates a **streaming segment**.

**All three evaluation modes and their API flags:**

```json
// Batch segment (daily evaluation)
"evaluationInfo": {
  "batch": { "enabled": true },
  "continuous": { "enabled": false },
  "synchronous": { "enabled": false }
}

// Streaming segment (continuous evaluation)
"evaluationInfo": {
  "batch": { "enabled": false },
  "continuous": { "enabled": true },
  "synchronous": { "enabled": false }
}

// Edge segment (synchronous, sub-millisecond)
"evaluationInfo": {
  "batch": { "enabled": false },
  "continuous": { "enabled": false },
  "synchronous": { "enabled": true }
}
```

**Choosing the right evaluation mode:**

| Mode | API Flag | Latency | Best For |
|---|---|---|---|
| *Batch* | `batch.enabled` | Hours | Large, complex audiences; daily campaigns |
| *Streaming* | `continuous.enabled` | Seconds | Real-time personalisation; trigger-based journeys |
| *Edge* | `synchronous.enabled` | Milliseconds | Same-page personalisation; web channel AJO |

**Streaming segmentation constraints:**

- Not all segment rule types are compatible with streaming evaluation (e.g., multi-entity joins require batch).
- If streaming evaluation cannot be applied to a rule, AEP *falls back to batch* automatically.
- Streaming segments are re-evaluated each time a qualifying new event is ingested for a profile — not on a fixed schedule.
